descript.abstract: State, which represents the state boundary, is a layer of the State of Minnesota BaseMap 2001 which consists of a number of individual data layers or themes digitized from USGS 7.5-minute quadrangles. These data layers fall into the following broad categories: transportation system, civil and political boundaries, and surface water. A description of the State layer is included in Section 5 of this document - Entity and Attribute Overview.
descript.purpose: The BaseMap was developed to fill a need at Mn/DOT for a continuous, statewide GIS base map of the transportation system.

timeperd.current: The original digitization was done during the 1990-1995 time period. For any given area, Mn/DOT used the most recent USGS 7.5-minute quadrangle available at that time. For BaseMap 2001, the following data layer was updated as recently as January 2001 using the most up-to-date available information: State.

procstep.procdesc:
Data Source: 1:24,000-scale USGS 7.5-minute quadrangles
Processing Steps: During the time period 1990-1995, the BaseMap data layers were digitized from USGS 7.5-minute quadrangles using MicroStation CADD. A total of 1745 quadrangles were digitized. For any given area, Mn/DOT used the most recent quadrangle available at that time. The digital MicroStation CADD files were converted from State Plane Coordinates to UTM and then converted into ARC/INFO coverages. The ARC/INFO files were merged into statewide, seamless coverages and then attributes were added.
